cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SY

This paper deals with a probabilistic extension of Datalog, which is a declarative programming language used in databases. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The paper also discusses the semantics of the language using probability theory, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a more principled approach towards defining the semantics, which involves combining declarative and probabilistic programming, making it relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the execution of the program, which could make it relevant to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the framework of infinite probabilistic databases, which could make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
